EXTENDED OUTLOOK
MONDAY TO THURSDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND MARITIME AGENCY
AT 152300 UTC
THIS PERIOD CARRIES LOWER THAN AVERAGE CONFIDENCE IN FCST DETAIL BUT SHOULD
START WITH A 998 LOW IN THE VICINITY OF SCOTLAND LEAVING A RIDGE OF HIGH
PRESSURE OVER SERN UK AND MUCH OF CONTINENTAL WERN EUROPE WHILE A MAJOR
990 LOW OCCUPIES THE MID-ATLANTIC W OF FITZROY AT THE SAME TIME. THE INITIAL
LOW SHOULD SOON LOSE ITS IDENTITY THROUGH TUESDAY WITH THE HIGH THEN DISPLACED
NWARDS MIDWEEK AS THE ATLANTIC LOW 979 ERODES ITS INFLUENCE IN THE SW APPROACHES.
THIS GENERAL NE-SW SPLIT SHOULD SEE OUT THE FCST PERIOD WITH THE LOW MAKING
UNCERTAIN SLOW AND ERRATIC EWARD PROGRESS LATER IN THE WORKING WEEK. THERE
IS A RISK OF GALES AND OCNL SEV GALES IN WERN NITON FOR MUCH OF THE PERIOD
WITH STRG WINDS PERHAPS EXTENDING TO AFFECT EERN ENGLISH CHANNEL NITON AND
THE SER N SEA FM MIDWEEK
